 towards the fantastic.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aFantastic, The, in literaturevCongresses. 0aFantasy fictionxHistory and criticismvCongresses. 0aLiterature and societyzEuropevCongresses. 0aScience fictionxHistory and criticismvCongresses. 4aFantasy. 4aScience-fiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aFantasy.  aScience Fiction.1 aBARR, MARLEEN S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBEEHLER, PAUL, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBÖGER, ASTRID, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBöger, Astrid, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCANADY, JACOBO, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCASALI, ARIANNA, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCLEAVES, WALLACE T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCORNILS, INGO, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDESZCZ-TRYHUBCZAK, JUSTYNA, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFILIPPO, PAUL DI, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGLASNER, LILY, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHERBE, SARAH, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHUANG, MINWEN, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKLAUS, ANNE, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKNEWITZ, SIMONE, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKOKORSKI, KARIN, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLENZ, CHRISTIAN, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMCMURRY, MARGARIDA, econtributor.4ctb4